{"id":23617,"title":"De Novo meningitis caused by Propionibacterium acnes in a patient with metastatic melanoma.","abstract":"Propionibacterium acnes is a known cause of postneurosurgical meningitis; however, it is rarely implicated in de novo meningitis. Herein we report a case of a 49-year-old male with de novo meningitis caused by P. acnes with metastatic melanoma as the only identified risk factor for his infection. ","date":"2014-03-12","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24478417","annotations":[{"name":"Infection","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Metastasis","weight":0.614946,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metastasis"},{"name":"Melanoma","weight":0.601159,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melanoma"},{"name":"Risk factor","weight":0.178431,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk_factor"},{"name":"Meningitis","weight":0.165579,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meningitis"},{"name":"Propionibacterium acnes","weight":0.12873,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propionibacterium_acnes"},{"name":"Risk","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Male","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Male"},{"name":"Propionibacterium","weight":0.0267211,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propionibacterium"},{"name":"Mutation","weight":0.0172523,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutation"}]}
